   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 21 of Marcus Aurelius Commodus Antoninus Augustus, Payni 12, for the account of Pachon. Paid by Petermouthis son of Kronion the son of Mystharion, his mother being Eudaimonis, for poll tax of year twenty-one, for the Linypheion quarter, twenty dr., total 20, plus ten obols for supplementary fees.</ab>
